  "description": "This high-density EEG dataset comprises resting-state and task-based recordings from 23 healthy volunteers collected during visual naming and spelling tasks. Participants performed two conditions (naming and spelling) with two runs each, viewing pictures of animals and objects while EEG was recorded using a 256-electrode system. The dataset supports investigation of dynamic functional brain network reorganization during language production and cognitive tasks.",
  "methods_description": "High-density EEG (256 electrodes, EGI system) was recorded at 1000 Hz sampling frequency with impedances maintained below 5 kΩ. Participants performed visual naming and spelling tasks with 74 stimuli per run, presented using E-Prime software. Speech responses were recorded via microphone and analyzed for onset detection using Praat v5.3.13.",
